div.div:
run_model_no_trade.py
First, run_model_no_trade() is run.
It loops through all countries specified in scenario_option "settings".
Imports each country as country_data (where country_data comes from each row of computer_readable_combined).
Then calls run_optimizer_for_country() passing in scenario_option and country_data for that country
run_optimizer_for_country():
Calls set_depending_on_option()
Then for each country, calls run_and_analyze_scenario() passing in
constants_for_params and
time_consts_for_params for the country in question

src/import_scripts_no_food_trade/create_[resource name]csv.py
for all resources (excluding data required for animal_populations.py,
which is an imperfection in the code which should be fixed eventually).
This creates a csv for each food resource in data/no_food_trade/processed_data/
Then it calls
src/import_scripts_no_food_trade/import_food_data.py
which combines everything to computer_readable_combined.csv

div.div: After single valued numeric or string values (consts_for_optimizer for the round) and monthly numeric values (time_consts) are computed, they are passed in to the optimizer in order to run the linear optimizations.

The Optimizer class is instantiated, and initialized with these constants, and either "to_humans" or "to_animals" optimization round is run.
Then, interpret_optimizer_results() is called with the pulp model object containing the results of the series of optimizations.

div.div: The Extractor and Interpreter are initialized.

The Extractor takes all the numeric values determined as the result of the optimizer (the amount of food to humans or the amount of food to animals), and turns them into normal python integers and floats rather than pulp's weird variable format.
The Interpreter converts the results to useful units and does some useful analysis, such as computing the percent of people fed, and the feed and biofuel sum.
The instantiation of the Interpreter (interpreted_results) contains all the data that are used for analysis and plotting this country\s results.
